In [10]:
#defining a function to calculate the emmotion of a newsheadline using RoBERTa from a DataFrame
def emotion(data, company):

  company=data.loc[data['title'].str.contains(company)]
  company.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

  company[['Negative', 'Neutral', 'Positive']]=0.0

  for ind1 in company.index:
    raw_text = tokenizer(company.loc[ind1]['title'], return_tensors='pt')
    output = model(**raw_text)
    scores = output[0][0].detach().numpy()
    scores = softmax(scores)
    
    #setting the values in the specific cells
    company.at[ind1, 'Negative']=scores[0]
    company.at[ind1, 'Neutral']=scores[1]
    company.at[ind1, 'Positive']=scores[2]
  
  return company

def find_average(df, emo_type):# a function that returns the average emotion for all news headlines for that company
  return np.average(df[emo_type])

def set_emotion(company_name, df ,compdf): #function that sets emotions to the "comp" dataframe
  compdf.at[company_name, 'Negative'] = find_average(df, 'Negative')
  compdf.at[company_name, 'Neutral'] = find_average(df, 'Neutral')
  compdf.at[company_name, 'Positive'] = find_average(df, 'Positive')

In [20]:
def graph(df): #A function that finds the Reputation Graph for a company using Linear Regression
  sns.regplot(x  = df.index, y= df['Negative'], fit_reg=True, scatter=False, color='forestgreen' )
  sns.regplot(x  = df.index, y= df['Neutral'], fit_reg=True, scatter=False, color='deeppink')
  sns.regplot(x  = df.index, y= df['Positive'], fit_reg=True, scatter=False, color='darkorange' )

  plt.xlabel('Count')
  plt.ylabel('Reputation ')

  plt.legend(["Negative", "Neutral", "Positive"]);
